First, rename variables ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao <- fao %>% select(Country.Group, Country)%>% rename(country_group = "Country.Group")%>% distinct() fao %>% filter(country_group == "Southern Europe") ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: Knit table with country groups and associated country groups ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} temp<-fao%>% group_by(country_group)%>% summarize(n=n())%>% arrange(desc(n)) half <-c(1:round(nrow(temp)/2)) knitr::kable(list(temp[half,], matrix(numeric(), nrow=0, ncol=1), temp[-half,]), caption = "# Coutnries by Country Groups")%>% kableExtra::kable_styling(font_size=15) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}

````` ::: ::: Nested sub regions within regions: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao%>% filter(str_detect(country_group, "[aA]nnex"))%>% group_by(country_group)%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao%>% filter(str_detect(country_group, "[aA]nnex"))%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ## Join Data - Combine data sets (marriage & debt) ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao%>% filter(str_detect(country_group, "[iI]ncome"))%>% group_by(country_group)%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao%>% filter(str_detect(country_group, "[iI]ncome"))%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao%>% filter(str_detect(country_group, "[Dd]evelop|OECD"))%>% group_by(country_group)%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao%>% filter(str_detect(country_group, "[Dd]evelop|OECD"))%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} major_regions<-c("Africa", "Asia", "Europe", "Americas", "Oceania", "Antarctic Region") fao%>% filter(country_group %in% major_regions)%>% summarise(n=n()) ``` ::: {.cell-output-display} `````{=html}
````` ::: ::: Create new categorical variables for the country groups for data set. ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} fao_regions_wide<-fao%>% filter(country_group!="World")%>% pivot_wider(names_from=country_group, values_from = 1)%>% unite("gp_annex", contains("Annex"), sep="", na.rm=TRUE, remove=TRUE)%>% unite("gp_major_region", any_of(major_regions), sep="", na.rm=TRUE, remove=TRUE)%>% unite("gp_income", contains("Income")|contains("income"), sep="", na.rm=TRUE, remove=TRUE)%>% unite("gp_develop", contains("Develop")|contains("OECD"), sep="", na.rm=TRUE, remove=TRUE)%>% select(Country, starts_with("gp")) ``` ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} nrow(birds) ``` ::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout} ``` [1] 30977 ``` ::: ::: ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} birds <- left_join(birds, fao_regions_wide, by = c("Area" = "Country")) ``` ::: Then we can summarize the data across the countries ::: {.cell} ```{.r .cell-code} eggs_chicken <- here("posts","_data","FAOSTAT_egg_chicken.csv") %>% read_csv() cattle <- here("posts","_data","FAOSTAT_egg_chicken.csv") %>% read_csv() dat <- left_join(eggs_chicken, cattle, by="Area") ``` ::: ##tapply(pseo$p50_earnings,pseo$deglevl,mean, na.rm = TRUE) ##cor(pseo$p50_earnings,pseo$year_postgrad, use="pairwise.complete.obs")
